Orlistat is a lipase inhibitor used in the treatment of obesity that works by inhibiting fat-metabolizing enzymes. It was approved by the FDA for use in combination with a reduced-calorie diet in 1999.[L11130] This drug is a generally well-tolerated and effective weight-loss aid and is now available in both over-the-counter[L31963] and prescription preparations, depending on the dosage quantity.[L11130]', '["A08AB01"]', '[]');
